{"source_key":"sha256-f88bd5c54ac5fbbfc982c6d403b2565f","record_index":864,"record_hash":"sha256:87dc6fda1903b224259cf793f9f29a2c8b8862e38e55731a44c5c8acb3c2ebe6","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:15:22.669Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 6abb67\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1417\nOutput:\n- warnings where the trail is weak or incomplete\n\nDo not default to dumping every message or every tool result. Exact records\nshould be available through drill-down.\n\nUseful sections:\n\n- Overview\n- Timeline\n- Prompts\n- Agent Claims\n- Validation\n- Missing Evidence\n- Evidence Drawer\n\nExact redacted records should be secondary. They exist for evidence and\ndebugging, not as the main review page.\n\n## MVP Page Contract\n\nThe first page should be a usable review surface, not a transcript explorer with\na nice header.\n\nFirst screen:\n\n- PR identity: `owner/repo#13936`, title, base branch, head branch, and source\n  GitHub URL\n- plain-language trail status: matched by PR, possible branch match, captured\n  metadata found, no metadata, no sessions, or unsupported\n- overview: human requests, agent claims, validation, touched files/areas when\n  available, and open questions or warnings\n- related sessions: compact list with agent/provider, capture time, match reason\n  badges, and evidence tier\n- selected session: turn timeline with highlighted turns\n- evidence drawer: grouped records and bounded exact-record drill-down\n- technical details drawer: generated-at time, metadata ref OID, projection\n  version, cache/fetch status, and diagnostic handles\n\nA reviewer should be able to answer these in under one minute:\n\n- why this trail is related to the PR\n- what the human asked the agent to do\n- what the agent claimed it changed\n- what validation ran, failed, or was skipped\n- which evidence can be expanded\n- what is still uncertain\n- what the page does not prove\n\nDefault behavior:\n\n- select the strongest direct/review-target session automatically\n- rank review-target matches above branch-only matches\n- dedupe sessions that match both review and branch targets\n- show branch-only sessions in a collapsed possible branch-related section if no\n  review-target match exists\n- show highlighted turns first, with chronological expansion a\n[TRUNCATED]\n  and validation blocks\n- collapse noisy tool output by default\n- highlight commands that changed files, ran tests, failed, or produced useful\n  evidence\n- make related branches, reviews, files, and validation attempts easy to scan\n- let the user expand exact redacted projection records when they need evidence\n- preserve chronological order without forcing the user to read every record\n\nThe UI should support both broad scanning and exact drill-down. A reviewer\nshould be able to start at the PR overview, jump into a highlighted turn, expand\nthe relevant tool call or assistant claim, then return to the overview without\nlosing context.\n\nExact projection records should remain available, but they should be treated as\nan evidence drawer, not the primary browsing mode.\n\n## Ranking And Highlighting\n\nThe page should rank or highlight likely relevant turns. Relevance is a product\ndecision above `but-agentlog`.\n\nGood signals:\n\n- direct review target observation\n- direct branch target observation\n- capture time near commits or PR updates\n- prompts mentioning the feature, bug, branch, or files\n- assistant claims about implementation or tests\n- tool calls that run tests, builds, formatters, or linters\n- later path or commit evidence, if added\n\nWeak signals:\n\n- backfilled turns with only capture-time environment snapshots\n- broad sessions that span unrelated work\n- sidecar review sessions that discuss the branch but did not implement it\n- turns related only through current branch state\n\nThe UI should expose why a turn is highlighted. Reviewers should not have to\nguess why a session appears.\n\n## Evidence Contract\n\nAgent Trail should feel evidential, not authoritative.\n\nEvery overview claim, warning, validation item, touched area, and open question\nshould have a source anchor to exact redacted projection records. If there is no\nsource anchor, label it as unavailable or omit it.\n\nSeparate agent claims from tool evidence:\n\n- use \"Agent claimed\" for assistant statements\n- use validation outcome labels for tool/command results\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:15:22.669Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}